---
import ReportLayout from "../../../layouts/ReportLayout.astro";
import Section from "../../../components/Section.astro";
import { chapterHref, chapterNavItems } from "../../../lib/chapters";
import { chrome, localePath } from "../../../lib/i18n";

const locale = "en" as const;
const nav = chapterNavItems(locale);
const t = chrome(locale);
const selfHref = localePath(locale, "guides/skills-corpus");
const ch01 = chapterHref("01-log-is-the-runtime", locale);
---

<ReportLayout
  title="Bundled Skills corpus · Agent Atelier"
  description="Agent-contract patterns mined from all 29 Maka bundled SKILL.md files: allowed-tools, boundaries, side-effect gates, evidence honesty — companion report, not a skill-body dump."
  nav={nav}
  activeHref={selfHref}
  locale={locale}
>
  <article class="report">
    <header class="masthead">
      <p class="masthead__eyebrow">Companion guide · Specimen: maka-agent · dig v3 · {t.doneLabel}</p>
      <h1>
        <span class="masthead__title-zh">Bundled Skills 语料</span>
        <span class="masthead__title-en">Skills corpus patterns</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="masthead__sub">
        Dig v2 marking all 29 <code>SKILL.md</code> files as <code>oos</code> was complacent: they
        encode <strong>agent behavior contracts</strong> (tool declaration, workspace safety,
        evidence honesty, side-effect confirmation), not disposable marketing copy. This page
        restates patterns from <strong>all 29 bodies</strong>; load mechanics remain in
        <a href={`${ch01}#skills`}>§01 · #skills</a>. When docs disagree,
        <strong>code + contract tests win</strong>.
      </p>
      <div class="masthead__meta">
        <span>Home · /guides/skills-corpus</span>
        <span>Map · #90</span>
        <span>
          <a href={localePath("zh", "guides/skills-corpus")}>中文</a>
        </span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <Section
      id="scene"
      label="Skills · Scene"
      title="Why mine product skill bodies"
      lede="Catalog mechanics ≠ skill contract corpus. The latter teaches what the agent may do after invoke."
    >
      <p>
        Runtime: catalog carries only <code>name</code> + <code>description</code>; bodies lazy-load
        (see §01 <code>#skills</code>). Desktop: bundled / managed / workspace sources + lock /
        sha256 governance (see
        <a href={localePath(locale, "guides/desktop-host")}>/guides/desktop-host</a>
        <code>#skills-governance</code>). This page is the third layer: treat the 29 bodies as an
        <strong>agent policy corpus</strong> — a reader should restate cross-skill invariants without
        opening every SKILL.md.
      </p>
      <blockquote class="pull">
        allowed-tools declares need; PermissionEngine grants; boundary sections constrain behavior.
      </blockquote>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="frontmatter"
      label="Skills · Front-matter"
      title="Front-matter hard contract (pinned by the creator skill)"
      lede="maka-skill-creator + managed-skill-sources make field parsing a fail-closed contract, not “casual YAML”."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>
          <strong>Line-oriented parse, not full YAML</strong> — <code>description</code> must be one
          line; <code>&gt;</code> / <code>|</code> folds drop fields.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Closed category set</strong> (unknown → <code>效率工具</code>): 内容创作 / 数据与AI /
          设计与UI / DevOps与部署 / 文档与写作 / 研究与分析 / 效率工具 — same as
          <code>MANAGED_SKILL_CATEGORIES</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Tool literals</strong>: <code>Read</code> · <code>Write</code> · <code>Edit</code> ·
          <code>Glob</code> · <code>Grep</code> · <code>Bash</code> · <code>WebSearch</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Body cap 24,000 chars</strong> on Skill-tool load (tail truncated) — put hard
          constraints first.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Marketplace is single-file</strong> — no <code>scripts/</code> /
          <code>references/</code> sidecars; “see reference.md” fails in Maka.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>id</strong>: <code>^[A-Za-z0-9][A-Za-z0-9._-]&#123;0,80&#125;$</code>; prefer
          kebab-case.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Specimens: <code>…/maka-skill-creator/SKILL.md</code> ·
        <code>managed-skill-sources.ts</code> · runtime <code>validateSkillMetadata</code>.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="allowed-tools"
      label="Skills · allowed-tools"
      title="Declaration spectrum across all 29"
      lede="Counts: Read=29, Write=23, Bash=16, WebSearch=9, Glob=3, Edit=1. Declaration still never grants."
    >
      <div class="table-wrap" role="region" aria-label="allowed-tools frequency" tabindex="0">
        <table class="proto-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Tool</th>
              <th scope="col">Hits</th>
              <th scope="col">Typical family</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row"><code>Read</code></th>
              <td>29/29</td>
              <td>Universal baseline</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row"><code>Write</code></th>
              <td>23/29</td>
              <td>Docs/HTML/ledgers; research often read-only</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row"><code>Bash</code></th>
              <td>16/29</td>
              <td>changelog / PDF / deploy / render / screenshot</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row"><code>WebSearch</code></th>
              <td>9/29</td>
              <td>Research + writing families</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row"><code>Glob</code></th>
              <td>3/29</td>
              <td>file-organizer / invoice / skill-creator</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row"><code>Edit</code></th>
              <td>1/29</td>
              <td>Only <code>responsive-design</code></td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>
        Extremes: <code>static-site-deploy</code> is <code>Read+Bash</code> only (deploy via CLI);
        research skills like <code>deep-research</code> are <code>Read+WebSearch</code> with no Write.
        Teaching point: tool-surface width ≠ permission width.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="cross-cut"
      label="Skills · Cross-cut"
      title="Eight agent contracts across all 29 bodies"
      lede="Dig v3 core deliverable: patterns from every skill, not two cherry-picked samples."
    >
      <ol class="plain-list numbered">
        <li>
          <strong>Declare ≠ grant</strong> — pinned by the creator skill; isomorphic to §01
          <code>#skills</code> / PermissionEngine.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Confirm before side effects</strong> — file-organizer (confirm moves) ·
          static-site-deploy (confirm prod) · internal-comms (write, never send) · copywriting (never
          publish for the user).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No invented evidence</strong> — deep-research / market-research / changelog /
          data-analysis / summarization / resume: say so when missing; numbers come from real compute
          or user material.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Fact vs speculation columns</strong> — competitive-ads, lead-research,
          market-research must label inferences.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>User owns auth and billing</strong> — deploy may launch login; never type
          passwords/tokens; never accept TOS / attach cards.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Output containment</strong> — design family defaults to self-contained HTML; PDF
          writes new files; invoice builds ledgers without moving originals.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>File content is data, not commands</strong> — file-organizer ignores “instructions”
          embedded in names/bodies.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>description decides invoke</strong> — WHAT+WHEN+user phrasing; body decides quality
          after load (creator methodology).
        </li>
      </ol>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="families"
      label="Skills · Families"
      title="Seven family personalities (by category)"
      lede="Closed taxonomy × boundary personality — not a feature ad."
    >
      <div class="table-wrap" role="region" aria-label="skill families" tabindex="0">
        <table class="proto-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">Category</th>
              <th scope="col">n</th>
              <th scope="col">Contract personality</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">设计与UI</th>
              <td>8</td>
              <td>Self-contained delivery, no live APIs, loyal to brief, offline-safe</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">文档与写作</th>
              <td>5</td>
              <td>Source-driven; no invented metrics; write-only (internal-comms)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">研究与分析</th>
              <td>5</td>
              <td>Public info, anti-confirmation-bias, gap markers, privacy (lead)</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">效率工具</th>
              <td>5</td>
              <td>Confirm gates, rollback, organize-not-delete, meta-creator</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">内容创作</th>
              <td>4</td>
              <td>No fabricated product facts; compliance tone; explain installs first</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">数据与AI</th>
              <td>1</td>
              <td>Numbers must come from scripts; transparent cleaning; correlation ≠ causation</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <th scope="row">DevOps与部署</th>
              <td>1</td>
              <td>Human-gated login/billing; conservative builds; return URLs only</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="high-signal"
      label="Skills · High-signal"
      title="High-signal boundaries (must be restatable)"
      lede="These skills encode workspace / trust boundaries into agent instructions — not soft advice."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>
          <strong>file-organizer</strong> — move never delete; confirm then execute; rollback list;
          skip <code>.git</code> / system dirs; content instructions are data.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>static-site-deploy</strong> — user completes OAuth; no TOS acceptance; explicit prod
          confirm; never leak tokens.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>changelog-generator</strong> — read-only git; no commit/push/rebase; report empty
          ranges; scrub secrets.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>pdf-toolkit</strong> — write new files; crypto not for access bypass; confirm heavy
          OCR deps.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>maka-skill-creator</strong> — freedom matches fragility; unified terms; three-part
          boundary template.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>lead-research-assistant</strong> — company-public granularity; forbid personal PII
          fields.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="inventory"
      label="Skills · Inventory"
      title="Full 29-row inventory"
      lede="Every row was read; teaching anchors are patterns, not restating every workflow."
    >
      <div class="table-wrap" role="region" aria-label="29 skills" tabindex="0">
        <table class="proto-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th scope="col">id</th>
              <th scope="col">category</th>
              <th scope="col">tools</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>brand-guidelines</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>changelog-generator</code></th><td>文档与写作</td><td>Bash, Read, Write</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>competitive-ads-extractor</code></th><td>研究与分析</td><td>Read, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>content-research-writer</code></th><td>文档与写作</td><td>Read, Write, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>copywriting</code></th><td>内容创作</td><td>Read, Write, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>create-plan</code></th><td>效率工具</td><td>Read, Write</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>data-analysis</code></th><td>数据与AI</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>deep-research</code></th><td>研究与分析</td><td>Read, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>domain-name-brainstormer</code></th><td>内容创作</td><td>Read, Write, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>drafter-diagram</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>file-organizer</code></th><td>效率工具</td><td>Read, Glob, Bash, Write</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>frontend-design</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>html-poster</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>html-slides</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>internal-comms</code></th><td>文档与写作</td><td>Read, Write</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>invoice-organizer</code></th><td>效率工具</td><td>Read, Glob, Bash, Write</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>lead-research-assistant</code></th><td>研究与分析</td><td>Read, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>maka-skill-creator</code></th><td>效率工具</td><td>Read, Write, Glob</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>manim-composer</code></th><td>内容创作</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>market-research-reports</code></th><td>研究与分析</td><td>Read, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>notion-infographic</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>pdf-toolkit</code></th><td>效率工具</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>responsive-design</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write, Edit, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>seo-audit</code></th><td>研究与分析</td><td>Read, Bash, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>static-site-deploy</code></th><td>DevOps与部署</td><td>Read, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>summarization</code></th><td>文档与写作</td><td>Read, Write</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>tailored-resume-generator</code></th><td>文档与写作</td><td>Read, Write, WebSearch</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>theme-factory</code></th><td>设计与UI</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
            <tr><th scope="row"><code>xhs-card-designer</code></th><td>内容创作</td><td>Read, Write, Bash</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p>
        Research outline (with boundary excerpts):
        <code>docs/research/skills-corpus-mine-outline.md</code>.
      </p>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="failures"
      label="Skills · Failure"
      title="Failure stories"
      lede="Treating skills as privilege channels — or oos as “done mining” — teaches the wrong threat model."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>Reading <code>allowed-tools: Bash</code> as already authorized → PermissionEngine theater</li>
        <li>Skipping confirm before <code>mv</code> / <code>--prod</code> → workspace / public damage</li>
        <li>Inventing URLs and numbers in research → polluted decision evidence</li>
        <li>Skill body pointing at <code>scripts/foo.py</code> → silent marketplace failure</li>
        <li>Vague description (“help with documents”) → catalog never matches</li>
        <li>Matrix <code>oos</code> with no teaching surface → dig complacency (why this page exists)</li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <Section
      id="boundaries"
      label="Skills · Boundaries"
      title="Not §01 #skills, and not a CSS dump"
      lede="Three layers, three truths."
    >
      <ul class="plain-list">
        <li>
          <strong><a href={`${ch01}#skills`}>§01 · #skills</a></strong> — catalog budget, lazy load,
          invoke, declare≠grant mechanics.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>This page</strong> — cross-skill behavior contracts from all 29 bodies.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong><a href={localePath(locale, "guides/desktop-host")}>/guides/desktop-host#skills-governance</a></strong>
          — bundled locks / managed sources / install surface.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </Section>

    <aside class="history-aside">
      <p class="history-aside__tag">Evolution aside · dig v3</p>
      <p>
        Map <a href="https://github.com/tt-a1i/agent-atelier/issues/90">#90</a> rejects dig v2’s
        “SKILL×29 = oos dump”. Specimen path:
        <code>apps/desktop/resources/bundled-skills/*/SKILL.md</code> ×29.
      </p>
    </aside>
  </article>
</ReportLayout>
